name: Almond
description: The almond is a species of tree native to Iran and surrounding countries, including the Levant. The almond is also the name of the edible and widely cultivated seed of this tree.

name: Apple
description: An apple is a round, edible fruit produced by an apple tree. Apple trees are cultivated worldwide and are the most widely grown species in the genus Malus.

name: Avocado
description: The avocado is a medium-sized, evergreen tree in the laurel family. It is native to the Americas and was first domesticated by Mesoamerican tribes more than 5,000 years ago.

name: Banana
description: Bananas are a healthy source of fiber, potassium, vitamin B6, vitamin C, and various antioxidants and phytonutrients

name: Cabbage
description: Cabbage, comprising several cultivars of Brassica oleracea, is a leafy green, red, or white biennial plant grown as an annual vegetable crop for its dense-leaved heads.

name: Carrot
description: The carrot is a root vegetable, typically orange in color, though purple, black, red, white, and yellow cultivars exist, all of which are domesticated forms of the wild carrot, Daucus carota, native to Europe and Southwestern Asia.

name: Cashew
description: The Cashew tree can grow as tall as 14 metres, but the dwarf cultivars, growing up to 6 m, prove more profitable, with earlier maturity and greater yields

name: Cauliflower
description: Cauliflower is one of several vegetables in the species Brassica oleracea in the genus Brassica, which is in the Brassicaceae family.

name: Cherry
description: A cherry is the fruit of many plants of the genus Prunus, and is a fleshy drupe.

name: Chili
description: Chili peppers are widely used in many cuisines as a spice to add heat to dishes.

name: Coconut
description: The coconut fruit is a drupe (a fleshy fruit with a hard stone containing the seed), and not a true nut.

name: Corn
description: Corn is a cereal grain first domesticated by indigenous peoples in southern Mexico about 10,000 years ago.

name: Cucumber
description: The cucumber is a widely-cultivated creeping vine plant in the family Cucurbitaceae that bears cylindrical to spherical fruits, which are used as culinary vegetables.

name: Garlic
description: Garlic is a bulbous plant belonging to the Allium family, which also includes onions, shallots, and leeks.

name: Green grape
description: Green grapes, also known as white grapes, are a variety of grapes that have a light green or yellowish-green color when ripe.

name: Guava
description: Guava is a common tropical fruit cultivated in many tropical and subtropical regions.

name: Hazelnut
description: The hazelnut is the fruit of the hazel tree and therefore includes any of the nuts deriving from species of the genus Corylus.

name: Kiwi
description: Kiwis are a nutrient-dense food â€” they are rich in in nutrients and low in calories.

name: Lettuce
description: Lettuce is most often grown as a leaf vegetable, but sometimes for its stem and seeds.

name: Mango
description: Botanically, mango is a drupe, consisting of an outer skin, a fleshy edible portion, and a central stone enclosing a single seed - also called stone fruit, like a plum, cherry, or peach.

name: Mangosteen
description: Mangosteen is a tropical evergreen tree with edible fruit native to tropical lands surrounding the Indian Ocean.

name: Okra
description: Okra is a flowering plant in the mallow family. It has edible green seed pods.

name: Onion
description: An onion, also known as the bulb onion or common onion, is a vegetable that is the most widely cultivated species of the genus Allium.

name: Orange
description: Oranges are a type of low calorie, highly nutritious citrus fruit.

name: Passion fruit
description: It is cultivated commercially in tropical and subtropical areas for its sweet, seedy fruit.

name: Peach
description: The peach is a deciduous tree first domesticated and cultivated in Zhejiang province of Eastern China.

name: Peanut
description: The peanut, also known as the groundnut, goober, pindar or monkey nut, is a legume crop grown mainly for its edible seeds.

name: Pear
description: Pears are fruits produced and consumed around the world, growing on a tree and harvested in late summer into mid-autumn.

name: Pinapple
description: It is the most economically significant plant in the family Bromeliaceae.

name: Pomegranate
description: The pomegranate was originally described throughout the Mediterranean region.

name: Potato
description: The potato is a starchy food, a tuber of the plant Solanum tuberosum and is a root vegetable native to the Americas.

name: Pumpkin
description: Pumpkin is a plump, nutritious orange vegetable, and a highly nutrient dense food.

name: Purple Grape
description: Purple grapes differ from their green or white counterparts in the Resveratrol they contain in their skin along with Quercetin.

name: Purple Onion
description: Purple onions also contain high levels of vitamin C, biotin, chromium, calcium, vitamin B6, folic acid, sulfur and fiber, which are good for health.

name: Salad
description: Salad greens contain Vitamin A, Vitamin C, beta-carotene, calcium, folate, fiber, and phytonutrients (see Table 1).

name: Strawberry
description: The fruit is widely appreciated for its characteristic aroma, bright red color, juicy texture, and sweetness.

name: Bell Pepper
description: Cultivars of the plant produce fruits in different colors, including red, yellow, orange, green, white, chocolate, candy cane striped, and purple.

name: Tomato
description: Labelled as a vegetable for nutritional purposes, tomatoes are a good source of vitamin C and the phytochemical lycopene.

name: Walnut
description: Walnuts are rich in heart-healthy fats and high in antioxidants.

name: Watermelon
description: Watermelon is a flowering plant species of the Cucurbitaceae family and the name of its edible fruit.
